leads.lead_text: Mericarps ovoid, beakless; plants usually with leaves at base and along stems; branches usually flexuose, sprawling, not or barely grooved
Mericarps with a short, stout, apical beak; plants leafless or with very few leaves at base only; branches erect, grooved and rather stiff
